title: Lesser Scaup Diving Duck: Photo Of The Day - San Diego, CA Patch
content:
If you have an awesome picture of nature, breathtaking scenery, kids caught being kids, a pet doing something funny or something unusual you happen to catch with your camera, we'd love to feature it on Patch.

We're looking for high-resolution, horizontal images that reflect the beauty that is San Diego County, and that show off your unique talents.

Send your photos to kristina.houck@patch.com. Be sure to include photo credit information, when and where the shot was taken, and any other details about what was going on.

title: NFT marketplace Magic Eden will pay you to buy and sell Solana NFTs - Yahoo Finance
content:
(Some Fortune Crypto pricing data is provided by Binance.)



NFT marketplace Magic Eden is going back to its Solana roots and paying traders to use the platform with a so-called “chapter two” initiative.

More from Fortune: 5 side hustles where you may earn over $20,000 per year—all while working from home Looking to make extra cash? This CD has a 5.15% APY right now Buying a house? Here's how much to save This is how much money you need to earn annually to comfortably buy a $600,000 home

It will include efforts to launch NFT aggregation on Solana, open source more of its code, and—for a limited time—pay traders a small bonus to buy and sell Solana NFTs.

Magic Eden has in recent months lost its long-held spot as the second-most-popular NFT marketplace behind OpenSea. It now holds only 2.1% of overall NFT market share by trading volume, according to CoinGecko. Although Magic Eden is the leading Solana marketplace, it has also faced pressure on the blockchain from upstart marketplace Tensor, which raised $3 million in a March seed round. Magic Eden was valued at $1.6 billion following a $130 million funding round last June.

In an effort to compete with OpenSea and Blur, which uses crypto airdrops to incentivize traders, Magic Eden will institute a -0.25% fee for NFTs. Essentially it will pay traders SOL whenever they sell a Solana NFT or whenever their offer to buy a Solana NFT is accepted. If you list an NFT for 100 SOL, or about $1924, on the marketplace, when it sells you will get 100.25 SOL, an extra $5, Magic Eden wrote in a Twitter thread. If you make an offer on an NFT worth 100 SOL, you will get an extra 0.25 SOL once your bid is accepted. The amount of SOL a user receives will be higher depending on the price of the NFT.

"Open sourcing our infrastructure we hope will continue to stimulate and encourage developers to use Magic Eden’s liquidity and tooling to grow the ecosystem as a whole," Zhuoxun Yin the co-Founder and Chief Operating Officer of Magic Eden said in a statement. "Additionally, the -0.25% maker fee was implemented to reward active members in the Magic Eden community. "

The new initiative and refocus on Solana comes as the marketplace has expanded to also list Ethereum and Bitcoin NFTs. The pivot back to Solana is also a vote of confidence in the blockchain, which has seen a flurry of new activity and is the third-most-active behind Bitcoin and Ethereum in terms of trading volume, according to CryptoSlam.

"Solana will always be where the Magic Eden journey started, and while we’ve taken steps to expand our offering to communities across other chains, we have been and are still long term convicted on the Solana ecosystem," Yin said in a statement.

Story continues

The initiative was mostly well received by NFT traders on Crypto Twitter. Others cheekily pointed out that the way Magic Eden wrote “chapter two” could be easily confused.

I read this as Chapter 11, Chapter II is way better 😆🎉 — Permissionless II (@Permissionless) May 25, 2023

I like the direction Magic Eden is taking. The recent moves are great for the NFT ecosystem and Solana NFTs. Healthy competition often fosters innovation and drives progress. #magiceden #nfts #solannft #nftmarketplace https://t.co/1OtXOyqXba — Zoe (@zozosfriesverse) May 25, 2023

whats genuinely amazing is i haven’t seen anyone besides like one or two people mad at magic eden for that announcement do you understand how insane that is ? — bunjil (@notbunjil) May 25, 2023

Magic Eden did not immediately respond to a request for comment from Fortune.

This story was originally featured on Fortune.com

title: Solana Faces Sell-Offs Amidst Breakthrough Above $20: Understanding the Market Dynamics - The Currency Analytics
content:
Solana, a prominent blockchain platform, recently experienced a series of sell-offs following its breakthrough above the $20 mark. This significant price milestone has triggered a range of reactions in the cryptocurrency market, leading to fluctuations in Solana’s value. In this article, we delve into the market dynamics surrounding Solana’s recent sell-offs, examining the factors influencing its performance and offering insights to a wider audience on the implications of these developments.

The sell-offs witnessed by Solana are a reflection of the inherent volatility of the cryptocurrency market. As digital assets gain popularity and attract investor attention, price movements can be swift and unpredictable. Solana’s breakthrough above $20 sparked enthusiasm among traders and investors, but it also triggered profit-taking by those who had acquired Solana at lower prices. These sell-offs, aimed at securing gains, led to temporary downward pressure on the asset’s price.

Understanding the market dynamics behind sell-offs is crucial for investors seeking to navigate the cryptocurrency landscape. Several factors contribute to the sell-off phenomenon, including market sentiment, profit-taking strategies, and external events impacting investor confidence. It is essential to assess these factors and conduct thorough market analysis to make informed investment decisions.

Volatility remains a characteristic feature of the cryptocurrency market, and Solana is no exception. Price fluctuations can be amplified by factors such as market speculation, regulatory developments, and broader economic trends. Traders and investors should be prepared for such volatility and approach their investment strategies with a long-term perspective.

While sell-offs can create short-term price fluctuations, they also present potential buying opportunities for investors. When a digital asset experiences a sell-off, it may become undervalued, providing an entry point for those seeking to establish or expand their positions. However, careful analysis and due diligence are crucial to avoid impulsive investment decisions during periods of heightened volatility.

The sell-offs witnessed by Solana also underscore the importance of blockchain technology and its potential impact on the financial landscape. Solana’s blockchain platform offers scalability, speed, and low transaction costs, making it an attractive option for decentralized applications and projects. Despite short-term price fluctuations, the underlying technology’s potential remains intact, and its adoption may continue to drive long-term value.

As the cryptocurrency market evolves, it is vital for investors and traders to stay informed and adapt their strategies accordingly. Monitoring market trends, conducting thorough research, and leveraging technical analysis can help investors navigate the volatile nature of the market and make informed decisions.

Understanding the market dynamics behind sell-offs is crucial for navigating the cryptocurrency landscape. Factors such as market sentiment, profit-taking strategies, and external events can influence investor behavior and contribute to price volatility. Therefore, conducting thorough market analysis, staying informed about industry trends, and adopting risk management strategies are essential for making informed investment decisions.

It is important for investors to recognize that volatility and sell-offs are common in the cryptocurrency market and should not be viewed as solely negative. During periods of market turbulence, digital assets like Solana may become undervalued, offering potential buying opportunities for those who believe in the long-term potential of the underlying technology.

Beyond the short-term price fluctuations, the underlying blockchain technology of Solana continues to hold immense promise. With its scalability, speed, and low transaction costs, Solana’s blockchain platform has the potential to revolutionize various industries and drive long-term value.

As the cryptocurrency market evolves, investors and traders must remain adaptable and responsive to changing market conditions. By staying informed, conducting thorough research, and leveraging technical analysis, they can navigate the market’s ups and downs with confidence.

It is worth noting that investing in cryptocurrencies carries risks, and individuals should carefully consider their risk tolerance and seek professional advice when necessary. However, for those who approach the market with caution, conduct due diligence, and embrace the long-term potential of innovative blockchain projects like Solana, the cryptocurrency market can offer exciting opportunities for growth and investment.

In summary, while the sell-offs experienced by Solana following its breakthrough above $20 may create short-term price fluctuations, they also present potential buying opportunities and should not overshadow the long-term potential of blockchain technology. By understanding market dynamics, conducting thorough analysis, and embracing a long-term perspective, investors can navigate the cryptocurrency market and seize the opportunities it presents.
